gomodel:SYNGO_288  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: p.36213: FIG. 1. Inwardly rectifying channel currents are seen when GIRK2 and GIRK3 are co-expressed in CHO-K1 cells. CHO-K1 cells expressing GIRK2 and GIRK3 were analyzed by patch clamp in the inside-out configuration in symmetrical 140 mM K\n\nrule: NAS_MFCC-BP\nrationale:\nProtein has voltage-gated ion channel activity and is localized in teh presynaptic membrane (show with high-resolution technique). The inference to term 'voltage-gated ion channel activity involved in regulation of presynaptic membrane potential (GO:0099508)' is trivial and non-controversial.\nPinf_CC:\n[P48542] SyNGO ID 285 (PMID:19558451, EM). Experimental description: Clone species not mentioned in MM: p.36211: CHO-K1 cells were transfected using TransIt.\n\n14/3/2017 Pim\n- Species of KCNJ6 construct traced back to PMID:8658170 where properties of mouse GIRK2 is compared to mutated GIRK2 in 'weaver' mice." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9425-2935" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_MF_288" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

